inspired his Breast ; Still in the Temple were his Vows addressed : Though he in Virtue's Paths , delighted , trod , Studious to please , and imitate his God ; The hallowed Altar , grateful , he surveyed , And there his lowly Adoration paid
the pale , childless Miser hoard up Wealth , And , trembling
the shining Over with guilty Care , To aggrandise some distant , worthless Heir
eyes with Joy the care-collected Hoard
eyes with Joy the care-collected Hoard
By Fortune's sudden Smiles to Madness fired
Who in the Scorners Seat , exulting
vaunt your impious Raillery for Wit
thy Ashes pay a silent Tear
the firm Basis of the Earth
